"},"cellVerticalMargin":{"left":"0","right":"0","center":"0"}},{"id":"348037cd-5139-48ea-86f2-3a03d32d4242","title":"Content Block 1","layout":"two-column","locked":false,"modules":[{"id":"module-ae640e95-5fca-45de-aaea-7ba97866a0d2","name":"","text":"<h1>Terms and Conditions</h1><h2>Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C.</h2><p>Welcome to the website of Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C. By accessing or using this website, you agree to the following Terms and Conditions. Please read them carefully. If you do not agree with these terms, you should not use this website.</p><h2>Use of This Website</h2><p>This website is provided for general informational purposes only. The content on this site is intended to help visitors learn more about Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C., our practice areas, legal services, attorneys, office locations, and general legal topics related to criminal defense and immigration law.</p><p>You agree to use this website only for lawful purposes and in a manner that does not interfere with the operation, security, or accessibility of the site.</p><h2>No Legal Advice</h2><p>The information provided on this website does not constitute legal advice and should not be relied upon as a substitute for speaking with an attorney about your specific situation. Every legal matter is different, and legal outcomes depend on the facts, applicable law, evidence, court procedures, and other circumstances.</p><p>You should consult directly with a qualified attorney before making decisions about any legal matter.</p><h2>No Attorney-Client Relationship</h2><p>Your use of this website, including submitting a contact form, sending an email, or calling our office, does not automatically create an attorney-client relationship with Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C.</p><p>An attorney-client relationship is formed only when our firm agrees to represent you and any required agreements are completed. Until that relationship is established, you should not send confidential, sensitive, or time-sensitive information through this website.</p><h2>Contact Forms and Communications</h2><p>If you submit information through a contact form, email, or other communication method, Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C. may use that information to respond to your inquiry, schedule a consultation, or provide information about our services.</p><p>Submitting a message does not guarantee that our firm will accept your case or provide legal representation. Please avoid including confidential or highly sensitive details unless you have first spoken directly with our office.</p><h2>No Guarantee of Results</h2><p>Past case results, testimonials, client reviews, or examples discussed on this website do not guarantee a similar outcome in any future case. Every case is unique, and Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C. makes no promises or guarantees regarding the outcome of any legal matter.</p><h2>Website Content</h2><p>Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C. makes reasonable efforts to keep website content accurate and up to date. However, laws, court rules, immigration policies, and legal procedures may change. We do not guarantee that all information on this website is current, complete, or applicable to your specific circumstances.</p><p>We may update, revise, or remove website content at any time without notice.</p><h2>Intellectual Property</h2><p>All content on this website, including text, images, graphics, logos, design elements, and other materials, is the property of Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C. or used with permission, unless otherwise stated.</p><p>You may view, print, or share website content for personal, non-commercial use only. You may not copy, reproduce, modify, distribute, or use website materials for commercial purposes without prior written permission from Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C.</p><h2>Third-Party Links</h2><p>This website may contain links to third-party websites for convenience or informational purposes. Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C. does not control and is not responsible for the content, accuracy, privacy practices, security, or policies of third-party websites.</p><p>Visiting third-party websites is at your own risk.</p><h2>Privacy</h2><p>Your use of this website is also subject to our Privacy Policy, which explains how we may collect, use, and protect information submitted through this website. Please review our Privacy Policy for more information.</p><h2>Limitation of Liability</h2><p>Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C. is not responsible for any damages or losses arising from your use of this website, reliance on website content, inability to access the website, or use of third-party links.</p><p>This website is provided “as is” without warranties of any kind, express or implied.</p><h2>Changes to These Terms</h2><p>Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C. may update these Terms and Conditions from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page. Continued use of this website after changes are posted means you accept the updated terms.</p><h2>Contact Information</h2><p>If you have questions about these Terms and Conditions or need legal assistance, please contact us:</p><p><strong>Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C.</strong><br><strong>Westminster:</strong> 10455 Sheridan Blvd., Suite 210, Westminster, CO 80020<br><strong>Brighton:</strong> 150 South 4th Avenue, Suite 200, Brighton, CO 80601<br><strong>Greeley:</strong> 609 8th Street, Suite 200, Greeley, CO 80631</p><p><strong>Phone:</strong> 720-373-3508<br><strong>Additional Phone:</strong> 720-216-4766<br><strong>Website:</strong> <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"http://www.brandonmarinoff.com\">www.brandonmarinoff.com</a></p><p><strong>Se Habla Español</strong></p><p><em>These Terms and Conditions are provided as general website content and should be reviewed by legal counsel to ensure compliance with applicable laws, regulations, and professional responsibility rules.</em></p>","type":"text","column":"left","settings":{"variant":"intro","mobi