"},"cellVerticalMargin":{"left":"0","right":"0","center":"0"}},{"id":"348037cd-5139-48ea-86f2-3a03d32d4242","title":"Content Block 1","layout":"two-column","locked":false,"modules":[{"id":"module-ae640e95-5fca-45de-aaea-7ba97866a0d2","name":"","text":"<h1>U.S. Citizenship</h1><h2>Your Final Step Toward the American Dream</h2><p>At <strong>Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C.</strong>, we believe becoming a United States citizen is one of the most meaningful milestones in an immigrant''s journey. U.S. citizenship offers not only legal security, but also the opportunity to fully participate in American society, protect your future, and create lasting opportunities for your family. Whether you have been a lawful permanent resident for many years or recently became eligible to apply, our experienced immigration attorneys are here to guide you through every step of the naturalization process with confidence and personalized legal support.</p><p>Naturalization involves much more than simply completing paperwork. Every application requires careful preparation, supporting documentation, and a thorough understanding of immigration law. Our legal team works closely with each client to evaluate eligibility, prepare accurate applications, anticipate potential challenges, and provide experienced guidance from the initial consultation through the Oath of Allegiance ceremony.</p><p></p><h1>What Is U.S. Citizenship?</h1><p>U.S. citizenship is the highest legal status available under United States immigration law. Individuals who become U.S. citizens enjoy important rights and privileges, including the right to vote, obtain a U.S. passport, petition for additional family members, seek certain government employment opportunities, and live and work permanently in the United States without immigration restrictions.</p><p>For most lawful permanent residents (Green Card holders), citizenship is obtained through the naturalization process. Eligibility generally depends on factors such as maintaining permanent resident status for the required period, demonstrating good moral character, meeting physical presence and continuous residence requirements, passing English and civics examinations (when required), and successfully completing a USCIS interview.</p>","type":"text","column":"left","settings":{"variant":"intro","mobileHidden":"false","desktopHidden":"false","verticalMargin":"0"}},{"id":"86aa7632-5560-46ab-b6f7-d401d6ff04a3","name":"Citizenship","text":"","type":"image","column":"right","settings":{"alt":"U.S. citizenship attorney","url":"https://astujhe2hvjqd0kf.public.blob.vercel-storage.com/APP_Assets/Image/1782660353963_US_Citizenshp_Services.png","size":"90","altText":"Image","linkUrl":"","imageUrl":"","maxWidth":"100","alignment":"center","maxWidthPx":"0","aspectRatio":"auto","borderRadius":"20","imageAssetId":"289","overlayOpacity":"0","verticalOffset":"0","borderThickness":"1","horizontalOffset":"0"}}],"alignment":"left","isPrivate":false,"marginTop":"0","background":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""},"cellHAlign":{"left":"left","right":"left"},"cellShadow":{"left":"none","right":"none"},"cellVAlign":{"left":"top","right":"top"},"cellOpacity":{"left":"1","right":"1"},"cellPadding":{"left":"18","right":"18"},"marginBottom":"0","mobileHidden":"false","mobileLayout":"stack","cellIsPrivate":{"left":"false","right":"false"},"desktopHidden":"false","overlayScreen":{"opacity":100,"background":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""}},"rowBorderColor":"#ffffff","rowBorderStyle":"solid","rowBorderWidth":"0","cellBackgrounds":{"left":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""},"right":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""}},"cellBorderColor":{"left":"#999999","right":"#999999"},"cellBorderStyle":{"left":"solid","right":"solid"},"cellBorderWidth":{"left":"0","right":"0"},"rowBorderRadius":"0","cellBorderRadius":{"left":"14","right":"14"},"cellMobileHidden":{"left":"false","right":"false"},"cellDesktopHidden":{"left":"false","right":"false"},"cellVerticalMargin":{"left":"0","right":"0"}},{"id":"section-1f91ac86-7404-42e9-a918-2e3386311456","title":"Content Block 2","layout":"two-column","locked":false,"modules":[{"id":"module-aeeafe39-cf70-4bfb-a824-7a8e28eb9f48","name":"","text":"<h2>Why Choose Marinoff &amp; Associates?</h2><h3>Experienced Naturalization Attorneys</h3><p>Our immigration attorneys have extensive experience guiding lawful permanent residents through the naturalization process. We understand the legal requirements, USCIS procedures, and documentation necessary to help clients pursue U.S. citizenship with confidence.</p><h3>Personalized Legal Guidance</h3><p>Every immigration journey is unique. We take the time to evaluate your residency history, immigration record, travel history, and individual circumstances to develop a legal strategy tailored to your eligibility and long-term goals.</p><h3>Thorough Preparation</h3><p>A successful naturalization application begins with careful preparation. We meticulously prepare and review your Form N-400, organize supporting documentation, and help ensure your application is accurate, complete, and ready for submission.</p><h3>Comprehensive Support</h3><p>From your initial consultation through your citizenship interview and Oath of Allegiance ceremony, we provide clear communication, honest advice, and responsive guidance every step of the way. We also help clients prepare for the English and civics examinations, giving them the confidence to approach the process successfully.</p><h3>Solutions for Complex Cases</h3><p>If your case involves prior criminal charges, extended travel outside the United States, previous immigration issues, or other potential obstacles, we carefully evaluate your circumstances and develop strategies to address challenges while protecting your eligibility whenever possible.</p><p>At <strong>Marinoff &amp; Associates, P.C.</strong>, we understand that becoming a U.S. citizen is more than completing an immigration application—it''s about securing your future, protecting your family, and fully embracing the opportunities and freedoms that come with American citizenship. Our commitment is to provide experienced legal representation, personalized attention, and compassionate support as you take this important final step in your immigration journey.</p>","type":"text","column":"right","settings":{"variant":"intro","mobileHidden":"false","desktopHidden":"false","verticalMargin":"0"}},{"id":"module-665ef090-ec37-4f92-b4b4-307af246259f","name":"","text":"","type":"image","column":"left","settings":{"alt":"Naturalization lawyer","url":"https://astujhe2hvjqd0kf.public.blob.vercel-storage.com/APP_Assets/Image/1782660755070_US_Citizenship_Marinoff_Law.png","size":"90","effect":"none","newTab":"false","linkUrl":"","variant":"image","alignment":"center","borderColor":"#0f4f8f","borderRadius":"18","mobileHidden":"false","desktopHidden":"false","verticalMargin":"0","verticalOffset":"0","borderThickness":"0","horizontalOffset":"0"}}],"alignment":"left","isPrivate":false,"marginTop":"0","background":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""},"cellHAlign":{"left":"left","right":"left"},"cellShadow":{"left":"none","right":"none"},"cellVAlign":{"left":"top","right":"top"},"cellOpacity":{"left":"1","right":"1"},"cellPadding":{"left":"18","right":"18"},"marginBottom":"0","mobileHidden":"false","mobileLayout":"stack","cellIsPrivate":{"left":"false","right":"false"},"desktopHidden":"false","overlayScreen":{"opacity":100,"background":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""}},"rowBorderColor":"#ffffff","rowBorderStyle":"solid","rowBorderWidth":"0","cellBackgrounds":{"left":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""},"right":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""}},"cellBorderColor":{"left":"transparent","right":"transparent"},"cellBorderStyle":{"left":"solid","right":"solid"},"cellBorderWidth":{"left":"0","right":"0"},"rowBorderRadius":"0","cellBorderRadius":{"left":"24","right":"24"},"cellMobileHidden":{"left":"false","right":"false"},"cellDesktopHidden":{"left":"false","right":"false"},"cellVerticalMargin":{"left":"0","right":"0"}},{"id":"9e3b8140-8553-46b4-a8db-d4aa25c9c1b0","title":"Content Block 3","layout":"two-column","locked":false,"modules":[{"id":"0f8bdd37-07c5-4e95-a5e1-ee936ec9026c","name":"","text":"<h2><strong>How We Can Help:</strong></h2><ul><li><p><strong>Eligibility Assessment: </strong>We will determine whether you meet the eligibility requirements for naturalization, which typically include being a lawful permanent resident for at least 5 years (3 years if married to a U.S. citizen), having good moral character, being able to speak and understand English, and passing a civics test on U.S. history and government.<strong><br><br></strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Filing the Naturalization Application (Form N-400): </strong>Our attorneys will assist you in completing the Form N-400 (Application for Naturalization), ensuring that all required information is accurate, and guide you in submitting it to U.S. Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS).<strong><br><br></strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Preparing for the Citizenship Interview:</strong> One of the most critical parts of the naturalization process is the citizenship interview. We will help you prepare for the interview, including reviewing your application, practicing for the civics test, and ensuring you are confident and ready for the questions from the USCIS officer.<strong><br><br></strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Civics and English Test Preparation: </strong>If you are required to take the civics and English language tests as part of the naturalization process, we offer resources and tips to help you pass the exams with ease.<strong><br><br></strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Assisting with Special Cases: </strong>If you have any complications in your case, such as criminal history, past immigration violations, or travel issues, we can help address these concerns before your naturalization interview and ensure that they do not impact your eligibility for citizenship.<strong><br><br></strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Attending the Naturalization Interview: </strong>We will help you prepare for and attend your naturalization interview with USCIS, ensuring that you understand the questions and are prepared to respond clearly and accurately.<strong><br><br></strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Post-Citizenship Assistance: </strong>Once you are granted citizenship, we can assist with applying for a U.S. passport and other post-citizenship benefits, ensuring that you are fully informed about your rights and responsibilities as a U.S. citizen.<strong><br><br></strong></p></li></ul><h2><strong>The Path to U.S. Citizenship</strong></h2><p><strong><br></strong>U.S. citizenship is an essential milestone for many immigrants, providing security, legal rights, and opportunities for you and your family. At Marinoff &amp; Associates, we are dedicated to helping you through the naturalization process, guiding you to become a U.S. citizen and achieve your immigration goals. Whether you have been a green card holder for years or are ready to take the next step, we offer expert advice and legal representation to help you succeed.</p><p>If you are ready to apply for U.S. citizenship or have questions about your eligibility, contact Marinoff &amp; Associates today. Our experienced attorneys will assist you in navigating the process and help you achieve the rights and privileges that come with becoming a U.S. citizen.<strong><br></strong></p>","type":"text","column":"left","settings":{"variant":"intro","mobileHidden":"false","desktopHidden":"false","verticalMargin":"0"}},{"id":"cf2379cd-c3b3-44ef-9271-6d4829d5bf8c","name":"","text":"","type":"image","column":"right","settings":{"alt":"Citizenship lawyer Colorado","url":"https://astujhe2hvjqd0kf.public.blob.vercel-storage.com/APP_Assets/Image/1782661362328_Brandon_Marinoff_-_Immigration_and_Criminal_Defense_Attorney.png","size":"90","effect":"none","newTab":"false","linkUrl":"","variant":"image","alignment":"center","borderColor":"#0f4f8f","borderRadius":"18","mobileHidden":"false","desktopHidden":"false","verticalMargin":"0","verticalOffset":"0","borderThickness":"0","horizontalOffset":"0"}}],"alignment":"left","isPrivate":false,"marginTop":"0","background":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""},"cellHAlign":{"left":"left","right":"left"},"cellShadow":{"left":"none","right":"none"},"cellVAlign":{"left":"top","right":"top"},"cellOpacity":{"left":"1","right":"1"},"cellPadding":{"left":"18","right":"18"},"marginBottom":"0","mobileHidden":"false","mobileLayout":"stack","cellIsPrivate":{"left":"false","right":"false"},"desktopHidden":"false","overlayScreen":{"opacity":100,"background":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""}},"rowBorderColor":"#ffffff","rowBorderStyle":"solid","rowBorderWidth":"0","cellBackgrounds":{"left":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""},"right":{"mode":"none","color":"#ffffff","color2":"#eaf4ff","opacity":100,"imageUrl":"","styleKey":"","imageAssetId":""}},"cellBorderColor":{"left":"transparent","right":"transparent"},"cellBorderStyle":{"left":"solid","right":"solid"},"cellBorderWidth":{"left":"0","right":"0"},"ro